      .column
        h2 Yan Margolin
        h3 Managing Partner
        p Yan Margolin is an attorney specializing in complex litigation, estate planning and business law.  He has handled appeals, commercial litigation, complex fraud and regulatory issues.  He is a member of the New York State Bar Association, and is admitted to practice in New York State and the Southern District of New York.  He is a fluent Russian speaker who lives and works here in the metropolitan community.

        p Yan Margolin is a graduate of the University of Southern California Law School, ranked 18th nationally by U.S. News and World Report. He obtained his B.A. From New York University, where he was the recipient of the presitigious Baird Scholarship.

      .column  
        h2 Neil Postrygacz
        h3 Of-counsel
        p Neil Postrygacz is a seasoned attorney with over ten years experience in commercial litigation, transactional corporate matters and entertainment contracts.  He has serviced sophisticated clients in New York and Florida, and is closely associated with the Law Offices of Yan Margolin.

        p A graduate of Cardozo Law School and Binghamton University, Neil resides in Brooklyn with his wife and two children.  He is fluent in Russian, Spanish and Yiddish. 

